WEBVTT

00:00.917 --> 00:02.377
Ah-hyuck!

00:02.460 --> 00:04.546
♪ H-h-h-hit it ♪

00:04.629 --> 00:06.381
♪ Like father, like son ♪

00:07.298 --> 00:08.591
♪ You're always number one ♪

00:08.675 --> 00:09.676
[both]
Yes!

00:09.759 --> 00:11.511
♪ There's buddies
There's pals ♪

00:11.594 --> 00:12.470
Yeah!

00:12.554 --> 00:14.848
♪ You always seem to work things out ♪

00:14.931 --> 00:16.641
♪ Can't you see you're two of a kind ♪

00:16.725 --> 00:18.727
♪ Lookin' for a real good time ♪

00:18.810 --> 00:19.644
Whoa!

00:20.311 --> 00:21.271
♪ A real good time ♪

00:21.354 --> 00:22.272
Aah!

00:22.689 --> 00:24.232
♪ Report to the Goof Troop ♪

00:24.315 --> 00:26.526
♪ And we'll always stick together ♪

00:26.609 --> 00:27.694
♪ Always stick together ♪

00:27.777 --> 00:29.362
♪ We're the Goof Troop ♪

00:29.446 --> 00:31.781
♪ The best of friends forever ♪

00:33.116 --> 00:35.493
♪ Side by side wherever we go ♪

00:35.577 --> 00:39.914
♪ We're always ready to roll ♪

00:39.998 --> 00:41.249
♪ Now gimme a beat ♪

00:41.332 --> 00:42.792
♪ We're the Goof Troop ♪

00:42.876 --> 00:45.462
♪ And we always stick together ♪

00:45.545 --> 00:46.379
Gawrsh!

00:46.463 --> 00:47.339
♪ We're the Goof Troop ♪

00:47.422 --> 00:50.550
♪ The best of friends forever ♪

00:51.468 --> 00:53.845
♪ Now we're calling everyone ♪

00:53.928 --> 00:55.889
♪ Come along and join the fun ♪

00:55.972 --> 00:56.973
♪ Report to the Goof Troop ♪

00:57.057 --> 00:58.850
♪ Baa ba doo da bop baa ba doo bop ♪

00:58.933 --> 00:59.809
Yeah!

01:01.644 --> 01:03.480
[dog barking]

01:09.319 --> 01:12.822
[man, on TV] On main street,
never leave your window open,

01:12.906 --> 01:14.491
never leave your lights off,

01:14.574 --> 01:18.620
and never order out for pizza,
because...

01:18.703 --> 01:21.790
-[woman screams]
-[chainsaw revving]

01:21.873 --> 01:22.957
He's back!

01:23.041 --> 01:24.918
The Mutilator on Main Street
part seven,

01:25.001 --> 01:26.920
now playing at a theater near you!

01:27.003 --> 01:29.255
-Radical!
-Sick!

01:29.339 --> 01:30.840
Classy. [burps]

01:30.924 --> 01:33.885
Hey, Peej, that's a top 10,
four-star must see.

01:33.968 --> 01:36.346
-Am I right, pal?
-Yuck!

01:36.429 --> 01:39.474
"Never order out for pizza because...

01:39.557 --> 01:40.809
He's back!"

01:40.892 --> 01:41.851
[chainsaw revving]

01:41.935 --> 01:43.561
Ahh!

01:43.645 --> 01:46.022
That kinda stuff makes a man outta ya.

01:46.106 --> 01:49.484
Oh, honestly, hon, why would anyone
want to watch that...

01:49.567 --> 01:50.568
-[shattering]
-Pistol!

01:50.652 --> 01:52.237
Get out of the hamper!

01:52.320 --> 01:55.073
It's worthless, a waste of time.

01:55.156 --> 01:58.159
-It's a child dementer.
-I can't believe it. Look! I found it!

01:58.243 --> 02:01.579
There's nothing wrong with a good scare
now and again, Snookums.

02:01.663 --> 02:04.582
[Peg] Oh, really, Pete?

02:04.666 --> 02:08.628
Gives a young man iron nerves
and bladder control. [burps]

02:08.712 --> 02:11.548
-We need that.
-Aw, I don't know, Max.

02:11.631 --> 02:14.217
[stammers] You see,
I got this model I wanna work on

02:14.300 --> 02:16.052
-and I don't, you know...
-[Pete] Hey!

02:16.136 --> 02:18.138
What's the matter, son?

02:18.221 --> 02:21.182
Feeling a little shaky?
Weak-kneed?

02:21.266 --> 02:23.268
A little yellow, maybe?

02:23.351 --> 02:27.439
[stammering] Well, uh, no.
No, Dad, no...

02:27.522 --> 02:31.026
Of course he's not!
Guts is our middle name, right, Peej?

02:31.109 --> 02:32.861
Yeah, Jelly Guts.

02:32.944 --> 02:35.030
[laughs] Knock yourself out.

02:35.113 --> 02:38.616
Uh, well, thanks, you know,
but we really couldn't--

02:38.700 --> 02:42.954
-His Dad will say no.
-Give me a break. No problem!

02:43.038 --> 02:45.582
-[Goofy] Forget it, Max!
-But why?

02:45.665 --> 02:48.418
Creepy movies don't agree with you, son.

02:48.501 --> 02:50.170
What are you talking about?

02:50.253 --> 02:53.006
Remember that old witch in
Snow White and the Seven Dwarves?

02:53.089 --> 02:56.426
Ah-hyuck! You were so scared
you had hiccups for a week!

02:56.509 --> 02:58.136
Snow White?

02:58.219 --> 03:00.722
No way! I mean...
That was, uh, Pickles!

03:00.805 --> 03:05.268
Max, you can't watch Grandma stuff
a chicken without getting faint.

03:05.852 --> 03:09.022
The past, Dad.
You're talking about the past.

03:09.105 --> 03:12.609
I'm 11 and a half. Nothing scares me.

03:13.443 --> 03:14.611
Except math tests.

03:14.694 --> 03:16.571
That's different, P.J.!

03:16.654 --> 03:19.783
Besides, his dad says
it's a part of manhood.

03:19.866 --> 03:21.534
I'm still working on boyhood.

03:21.618 --> 03:23.286
Manhood, huh? So...

03:23.370 --> 03:26.539
[Max] So, so, I'm old enough to do this.

03:26.623 --> 03:29.292
-Right, Peej?
-[stammers] Well, I, you know, I...

03:29.376 --> 03:31.670
-Gonna give you hiccups.
-Aw, I can handle it, Dad.

03:31.753 --> 03:35.256
-You sure?
-Posilutely, you got it, Dad.

03:35.340 --> 03:39.177
-OK, Max. Go for it.
-Yes!

03:39.260 --> 03:41.888
Ah, I'm not really sure about this, Max.

03:41.971 --> 03:45.058
-But be home for supper!
-I could help with supp...

03:45.141 --> 03:50.355
-[chuckles] Kids.
-[TV warbling]

03:50.855 --> 03:51.815
Ah-hyuck!

03:51.898 --> 03:55.318
Now, let me see, a sandwich?

03:55.402 --> 03:58.363
With ketchup and mustard and olives...

03:58.446 --> 04:00.156
[meows]

04:00.240 --> 04:01.282
Now all I need is...

04:01.366 --> 04:04.035
Huh? Max!

04:04.119 --> 04:05.453
[meows]

04:07.580 --> 04:10.583
Gonna need some Swiss cheese,
pig knuckles and tomatoes

04:10.667 --> 04:14.963
and pickled onions, bread
and let's see, um...

04:17.882 --> 04:19.009
Huh?

04:23.388 --> 04:24.514
Hmm.

04:29.561 --> 04:32.105
Ah-hyuck! I knew I forgot something!

04:40.613 --> 04:44.200
Hmm, gotta get me a roomier car.

04:44.284 --> 04:47.537
Howdy, neighbor!
Your yard's looking peachy!

04:47.620 --> 04:50.874
-Thanks, neighbor. Whoa!
-[barks]

04:50.957 --> 04:53.084
Ha! Wasn't even close!

04:53.585 --> 04:54.669
[yells in pain]

04:55.587 --> 04:57.422
I thought you were gonna cut this!

04:57.505 --> 04:58.923
It's hanging onto my property!

04:59.007 --> 05:00.842
Cutting into my air space.

05:00.925 --> 05:04.554
Later! Gotta go to all-night market
before it closes.

05:04.637 --> 05:07.265
Hmm, what a goof!

05:11.019 --> 05:15.023
Yeah, come on, big screen,
six track, total experience.

05:15.106 --> 05:17.275
-[P.J.] Oh, Max!
-Peej!

05:17.359 --> 05:19.861
[Goofy]
Potatoes, onions, pickled herring...

05:19.944 --> 05:23.073
Oops! [laughs] Can't forget the pepperoni!

05:30.288 --> 05:31.748
Whoopsie Daisy!

05:34.459 --> 05:38.046
-That'll be $87.53.
-Ah-hyuck!

05:38.129 --> 05:39.714
[woman screaming on screen]

05:39.798 --> 05:43.468
Ah, ripping! I gotta tell ya,
you were right, Max!

05:43.551 --> 05:47.097
Man, this is great.
It's, like, not scary at all.

05:47.847 --> 05:49.557
Uh, Max?

05:49.641 --> 05:51.434
[hiccuping]

05:51.518 --> 05:54.354
Come on, shh!
You're missing the best part.

05:54.437 --> 05:55.772
-[chainsaw revving]
-[splattering]

05:55.855 --> 05:57.440
[screams]

05:57.524 --> 05:59.359
[hiccuping]

06:02.112 --> 06:03.613
[imitating chainsaw noises]

06:03.697 --> 06:05.865
[chuckles] Awesome!

06:05.949 --> 06:08.159
[hiccups] Is it over?

06:08.243 --> 06:10.286
-Yeah, it's over.
-Totally?

06:10.370 --> 06:11.788
Yeah, totally.

06:14.749 --> 06:17.544
Hey, I just wanted to get
the last kernel, OK?

06:17.627 --> 06:18.837
[scoffs] Yeah, right.

06:18.920 --> 06:20.964
Well, at least I didn't
freak out in the lobby.

06:21.047 --> 06:23.133
Come on, P.J., admit it! You were scared!

06:23.216 --> 06:24.759
-What, me, scared?
-Yeah, you.

06:24.843 --> 06:27.262
Ha! Just 'cause you were
hiding under the seat!

06:27.345 --> 06:28.805
[Max] No way! I wasn't scared, I mean...

06:28.888 --> 06:30.765
What about the part with the chainsaw?

06:30.849 --> 06:33.268
-Ah, kid's stuff!
-Oh, yeah, and the meat locker scene?

06:33.351 --> 06:34.269
Piece of cake!

06:34.352 --> 06:37.480
Hey, man, what about
the stuff in the bathtub?

06:37.564 --> 06:38.773
[both] Killer!

06:38.857 --> 06:42.402
[loud crash]

06:42.485 --> 06:44.070
-What was that?
-I don't know.

06:44.154 --> 06:47.240
-Maybe we'd better go home.
-[stammering] Home's good.

06:47.323 --> 06:48.908
[Max] I mean, not that I'm scared
or anything...

06:48.992 --> 06:50.744
-Oh, no, me neither...
-[growling]

06:50.827 --> 06:52.537
[cat meowing]

06:52.620 --> 06:54.664
-But it is kinda late.
-Oh, yeah, it's late.

06:54.748 --> 06:56.958
And I wouldn't want my dad to worry and...

06:57.042 --> 06:57.917
[thunder rumbling]

06:58.001 --> 07:01.838
-[Max] I'll race ya!
-[P.J.] Max! Wait for me!

07:04.632 --> 07:06.551
[thunder cracking]

07:10.013 --> 07:12.265
[Max and P.J. screaming]

07:15.352 --> 07:18.438
[panting] We made it!

07:18.521 --> 07:19.773
How was the movie?

07:19.856 --> 07:22.359
Oh, yeah, you should have seen it, Dad!

07:22.442 --> 07:25.528
The Mutilator, he had this
big old knife and he was...

07:25.612 --> 07:26.696
[screaming]

07:26.780 --> 07:28.031
[hiccuping]

07:28.114 --> 07:29.532
-Was that a hiccup?
-No!

07:29.616 --> 07:30.450
[gasps]

07:30.533 --> 07:33.286
Uh, hey, Peej, you wanna stay overnight?

07:33.370 --> 07:36.122
Hey, cool! I'll call and see if it's OK.

07:36.664 --> 07:37.540
-[chopping]
-[gasps]

07:37.624 --> 07:40.669
Hey, wait, I'll help you dial.

07:40.752 --> 07:42.671
[ringing]

07:42.754 --> 07:45.173
Don't put mustard in the dog's ear, honey.

07:45.256 --> 07:47.175
[laughs] Get the phone!

07:47.258 --> 07:49.761
[Pete] Oh, sure, Sweetums. [chuckles]

07:50.011 --> 07:52.555
Hello? Oh, P.J.

07:52.639 --> 07:55.475
Mmm-hmm. Sure, sure you can stay over.

07:55.558 --> 07:58.228
Spend the week. They can adopt you
as far as I could...

07:58.311 --> 07:59.729
Oh, how was the movie?

07:59.813 --> 08:01.398
Did it scare you?

08:01.481 --> 08:03.525
Hey, no biggie, Pop!

08:03.608 --> 08:05.151
Just another flick!

08:05.235 --> 08:07.612
Just another flick? Are you kidding?

08:07.696 --> 08:11.074
-Why, that's a true story.
-It is?

08:11.157 --> 08:14.035
Down in Amarilla. Saw it on the news.

08:14.119 --> 08:16.746
He came in through
the bedroom window.

08:16.830 --> 08:19.916
-He did?
-Sleep tight, son!

08:20.000 --> 08:22.544
[cackling]

08:22.627 --> 08:24.462
What are you cackling about?

08:24.546 --> 08:29.175
Oh, nothing, dear. Absolutely nothing.

08:29.968 --> 08:31.636
[Max] No way! It never happened!

08:31.720 --> 08:32.846
-[P.J.] Did to!
-[Max] Did not!

08:32.929 --> 08:33.805
-[P.J.] Did to!
-[Max] Did not!

08:33.888 --> 08:34.764
-[P.J.] Did to!
-[Max] Did not!

08:34.848 --> 08:37.475
[P.J.] Hey, are you calling my dad bogus?

08:37.559 --> 08:39.728
According to the Solemn
Rules of Sleepover,

08:39.811 --> 08:41.646
there's only one way to settle this...

08:41.730 --> 08:43.481
[both] Pillow fight!

08:47.944 --> 08:49.154
[chuckles]

08:49.237 --> 08:53.408
These boys won't sleep much tonight!
[laughs]

08:54.117 --> 08:56.494
[screeching]

08:56.578 --> 08:59.414
-[both shouting]
-Wait! Did you hear something?

08:59.497 --> 09:01.499
Come on, quit fooling around, Max.

09:01.583 --> 09:02.959
I'm not fooling around! Listen!

09:03.043 --> 09:06.296
[screeching]

09:06.379 --> 09:09.466
-That's not you?
-It's not me, is it you?

09:09.549 --> 09:10.592
Uh-uh.

09:10.675 --> 09:14.512
Well, if it's not me,
and it's not you, then...

09:15.347 --> 09:17.057
[both scream]

09:17.140 --> 09:20.018
[laughing] I love kids.

09:21.478 --> 09:23.730
Oh, ain't she a beaut?

09:23.813 --> 09:26.733
The perfect bedtime snackeroo.

09:26.816 --> 09:28.276
[meows]

09:31.404 --> 09:32.697
Careful, kitty!

09:33.531 --> 09:36.451
[muttering]

09:39.954 --> 09:40.789
[meows]

09:40.872 --> 09:42.999
-[Max] Go look!
-[P.J.] No way! You look!

09:43.083 --> 09:44.668
[Max] I'm not gonna look! You look!

09:44.751 --> 09:47.921
-[P.J.] It was your idea!
-[Max] Well, at least move over!

09:48.004 --> 09:49.422
[P.J.] Hey, quit shoving!

09:49.506 --> 09:50.924
[Max] Me? You're the one that's shoving!

09:51.007 --> 09:52.592
[alarm ringing]

09:52.676 --> 09:53.510
[meows]

09:54.260 --> 09:55.261
[screeching]

09:55.345 --> 09:57.347
[both screaming]

10:00.266 --> 10:02.686
[growls]

10:02.769 --> 10:04.521
[both] It's the Mutilator!

10:04.604 --> 10:06.856
[laughs]

10:16.449 --> 10:18.410
[Max and P.J. screaming]

10:18.493 --> 10:21.246
-Huh?
-[both] The Mutilator's here!

10:24.833 --> 10:25.709
[grunts]

10:28.086 --> 10:29.087
Gawrsh!

10:29.170 --> 10:32.048
Oh, he's gonna get us
just like he got all those...

10:32.132 --> 10:33.717
-[shivering]
-Campers?

10:33.800 --> 10:36.219
-Yeah!
-See what that movie did to you?

10:36.302 --> 10:37.262
It's real.

10:37.345 --> 10:40.181
The Mutilator's outside,
he's trying to get in!

10:40.265 --> 10:41.516
I think he ate your cat.

10:41.599 --> 10:43.893
Oh, he did, did he?

10:45.103 --> 10:48.148
Well, then I guess I'd better
have a little lookie-see.

10:48.481 --> 10:49.816
Whoa!

10:49.899 --> 10:51.359
[Max] Be careful, Dad.

10:51.443 --> 10:52.277
[crashing]

10:52.360 --> 10:54.279
Watch your back, Mr. G.

10:54.362 --> 10:58.033
[laughing]

10:58.116 --> 11:01.870
Well, that oughta put hair
on their chinny-chin-chins!

11:01.953 --> 11:04.497
[laughs] Whoa!

11:10.253 --> 11:11.838
[grunts]

11:14.507 --> 11:15.550
Whoa!

11:17.344 --> 11:18.762
Goofy!

11:18.845 --> 11:20.347
[snoring softly]

11:21.056 --> 11:21.931
[door opens]

11:27.479 --> 11:28.480
[crackling]

11:31.900 --> 11:32.901
[shrieking]

11:32.984 --> 11:34.235
[screams]

11:35.987 --> 11:37.322
Ow!

11:41.618 --> 11:42.452
[crash]

11:42.744 --> 11:43.995
You OK?

11:45.663 --> 11:47.665
Ah-hyuck! Found kitty.

11:50.251 --> 11:53.880
Creepy movies, nothing but trouble,
wrecked my sandwich.

11:57.759 --> 11:58.843
Gawrsh!

12:03.348 --> 12:04.933
[thunder cracking]

12:06.017 --> 12:07.310
[scatting]

12:10.855 --> 12:13.024
[leaves rustling]

12:15.110 --> 12:17.946
The Mutilator! Ah-hyuck!

12:19.030 --> 12:20.865
[scatting]

12:24.577 --> 12:26.121
Aw, shucks!

12:34.629 --> 12:37.507
-What's that?
-It's, it's the Mutilator!

12:41.845 --> 12:44.723
Hey, boys, let me in! Let me in!

12:49.936 --> 12:51.396
I don't hear him anymore.

12:51.479 --> 12:54.232
-Maybe he's gone.
-You wish.

12:54.315 --> 12:55.734
[thunderclap]

13:07.328 --> 13:09.664
Just what I needed. Whoops!

13:12.542 --> 13:13.710
[branch snapping]

13:15.128 --> 13:18.381
Come to Papa, little light!
[makes kissing sounds]

13:26.431 --> 13:28.183
[meows]

13:28.266 --> 13:30.602
[snickering]

13:37.192 --> 13:38.568
[both gasp]

13:38.651 --> 13:40.653
[yelling]

13:42.781 --> 13:44.199
[Max] Cops! Call the cops!

13:48.870 --> 13:50.288
Whoa!

13:51.539 --> 13:55.168
-[electricity crackling]
-[shrieking]

13:55.251 --> 13:58.171
[gasps] P.J., the phone's dead!

13:58.254 --> 13:59.923
Just like we're gonna be!

14:00.173 --> 14:02.258
Where's my dad! Where's my dad!

14:04.010 --> 14:06.721
[thunder rumbles]

14:06.805 --> 14:09.891
Ruined a perfectly good pair of pajamas.

14:10.975 --> 14:12.894
Whoa!

14:18.149 --> 14:19.651
[both] Oh, no!

14:21.569 --> 14:22.987
[gasps] It's him!

14:23.071 --> 14:25.073
[muffled] Max! P.J.!

14:25.156 --> 14:28.660
[both] He knows your name!

14:28.743 --> 14:31.579
[both] Upstairs, upstairs, upstairs!

14:31.663 --> 14:33.748
OK, I'll meet ya!

14:56.312 --> 14:57.313
He's on the roof!

14:57.647 --> 15:00.358
[both] Downstairs, downstairs, downstairs!

15:03.445 --> 15:05.321
[chewing]

15:05.405 --> 15:06.823
[Goofy] Hey, that's mine!

15:06.948 --> 15:09.784
Blasted cat! Hey, get away from there.

15:11.661 --> 15:13.204
[yells]

15:13.288 --> 15:15.123
[laughing]

15:15.206 --> 15:19.002
Those kids sure are cute
when they're petrified. [laughing]

15:25.175 --> 15:26.009
Yow!

15:27.260 --> 15:29.846
Ah, where have you been?

15:31.306 --> 15:33.350
I wasn't out scaring the kids.

15:33.433 --> 15:36.144
[Peg] Mmm-mmm.
I don't think that's very funny.

15:36.227 --> 15:39.856
Now you go over there
and tell them you're sorry.

15:39.939 --> 15:42.150
-Oh, but, Peg...
-But nothing!

15:42.817 --> 15:44.611
Yes, Snookums.

15:45.570 --> 15:49.074
Wonder what good the little weasels are
if you can't have a little fun.

15:49.157 --> 15:50.158
[shattering]

15:50.241 --> 15:51.785
Aw, shucks!

15:51.868 --> 15:53.620
Now I'm gonna have
to make a whole new sandwich

15:53.703 --> 15:54.954
is what I'll have to do.

15:56.790 --> 15:59.125
[muttering] Hmm,
I don't care what anyone says.

15:59.250 --> 16:02.587
A good shock to the system's
good for you every now and then.

16:05.882 --> 16:07.300
[thunder cracking]

16:07.384 --> 16:08.802
[gasps]

16:09.636 --> 16:11.304
[yells]

16:18.561 --> 16:21.147
Gotta get to your house, Peej,
it's our only chance.

16:21.231 --> 16:23.191
-[stammering] OK. OK.
-All right,

16:23.274 --> 16:24.901
on the count of three,
we run for it.

16:25.026 --> 16:26.820
-You ready?
-Ready.

16:26.903 --> 16:27.779
Three!

16:30.240 --> 16:32.826
[both yelling]

16:32.951 --> 16:35.036
[both] Dead body!

16:35.120 --> 16:37.414
[both yelling]

16:45.588 --> 16:49.009
[grunts] Well, next time I'm going
to have to get myself another key

16:49.134 --> 16:50.593
and put it somewhere.

16:50.719 --> 16:52.095
Whoa!

16:57.267 --> 16:58.518
-[crash]
-Ow!

16:59.019 --> 17:02.939
Ow! Ooh! Ouch!

17:03.023 --> 17:04.482
Hey! Ow!

17:05.150 --> 17:06.818
[Goofy] Oh, my toe!

17:08.028 --> 17:08.987
Quick! The attic!

17:09.863 --> 17:11.865
[P.J.] I can't take this anymore!

17:14.242 --> 17:17.620
[panting] Made it!

17:17.704 --> 17:19.497
[P.J.] Max! Max!

17:19.581 --> 17:21.166
-Who is it?
-It's me.

17:21.249 --> 17:22.208
"Me" who?

17:22.792 --> 17:24.919
-[match sparking]
-There, that's better.

17:25.003 --> 17:26.921
Now, if I could just get in.

17:34.888 --> 17:36.514
[clattering]

17:40.435 --> 17:42.312
[Goofy] Ah-hyuck!

17:42.896 --> 17:44.773
[chainsaw revving]

17:45.440 --> 17:47.400
He's here, in the house!

17:48.693 --> 17:50.487
-What are we gonna do now?
-[hiccups]

17:50.612 --> 17:51.571
No kidding!

17:51.654 --> 17:53.323
[both hiccuping]

17:57.118 --> 17:58.995
-[both hiccuping]
-[chainsaw revving]

18:07.045 --> 18:09.422
Ah-hyuck! Taller than I thought.

18:11.466 --> 18:13.426
[sniffing] Now let's see.

18:13.843 --> 18:18.264
Cream cheese, onions,
pepperoni, sweet potatoes,

18:18.348 --> 18:20.934
bologna, mustard, mayonnaise...

18:29.567 --> 18:31.778
[meows]

18:33.613 --> 18:36.032
[slurps] Oh, boy!

18:36.741 --> 18:38.118
Whoa!

18:40.995 --> 18:43.248
-[yelling]
-[crash]

18:43.331 --> 18:46.376
[gasps] He's got Dad! [hiccuping]

18:46.459 --> 18:47.293
And we're next! [hiccups]

18:47.377 --> 18:49.963
-Let's hide! [hiccups]
-No!

18:50.046 --> 18:52.257
-No? [hiccups]
-No.

18:52.507 --> 18:55.552
No more running, Peej.
I've got to save my dad!

18:55.635 --> 18:57.387
You really going down there?

18:58.096 --> 18:59.973
I got to, Peej.

19:00.598 --> 19:02.517
-Max!
-Yeah?

19:02.809 --> 19:04.310
You lost your hiccups.

19:06.563 --> 19:07.689
So did you.

19:08.815 --> 19:11.609
[scatting]

19:13.737 --> 19:15.780
-Ready?
-No. But, let's do it anyway!

19:19.367 --> 19:21.411
[Max] He's bigger than I thought!

19:21.870 --> 19:23.747
Does this mean sleepover's over?

19:27.625 --> 19:29.002
-[both] Gotcha!
-[Goofy] Wha...

19:29.085 --> 19:30.795
[Goofy, muffled] Hey, what's going on?

19:30.879 --> 19:33.423
-[Max] This is for my dad, creep!
-[Goofy] Oh!

19:33.506 --> 19:35.884
-[P.J.] And this is for Mr. G.!
-[Goofy] Oof!

19:35.967 --> 19:37.594
[cat screeches]

19:37.677 --> 19:39.804
[all yelling]

19:44.309 --> 19:46.811
-And this is for my dad!
-[Goofy] Ow.

19:46.895 --> 19:49.564
-And this is for my dad!
-[Goofy] Oh!

19:49.689 --> 19:52.567
And this is for my dad!

19:52.692 --> 19:55.111
Uh, Max? It is your dad!

19:55.195 --> 19:56.988
And this is for my...

19:58.198 --> 19:59.324
Dad?

20:00.450 --> 20:02.619
Your dad's the Mutilator?

20:03.119 --> 20:03.995
Cool!

20:04.579 --> 20:05.914
Uh, is he dead?

20:08.083 --> 20:09.626
[stammering] Uh, sorry, Dad.

20:10.168 --> 20:11.753
But, we thought he got you.

20:11.836 --> 20:14.381
Max, there is no Mutilator.

20:14.506 --> 20:18.009
-I knew that.
-We didn't know that, Max.

20:18.093 --> 20:20.387
Yeah, you're right.
We didn't know that.

20:20.470 --> 20:22.472
We acted like
a couple of chickens.

20:22.555 --> 20:25.392
Yeah, we acted like a couple
of weak-kneed,

20:25.475 --> 20:29.521
yellow-bellied, rubber-legged,
Lily-livered, back-pedaling...

20:29.604 --> 20:31.189
That'll do it, Peej.

20:31.314 --> 20:32.273
-OK?
-OK.

20:32.732 --> 20:35.735
Now, wait a minute.
You boys were brave.

20:35.819 --> 20:37.779
You saved me from the Mutilator...

20:38.405 --> 20:40.031
Er, kind of.

20:41.783 --> 20:45.620
-Yeah, we did!
-Yeah, P.J.! We are brave!

20:45.745 --> 20:46.788
Cool, we could have saved him.

20:46.913 --> 20:48.873
Yeah, we could've saved him
for sure, no problem.

20:48.998 --> 20:51.292
[gasps] What about the body?

20:51.459 --> 20:54.587
-What body?
-[both] Under the tree branch!

20:54.713 --> 20:56.006
Tree branch!

20:56.131 --> 21:00.093
Oh, sweetie, do you want some coffee?
Aspirin?

21:00.218 --> 21:02.303
What do you want, darling?

21:02.387 --> 21:06.933
Can I have a waffle iron
for Christmas, Momma?

21:07.058 --> 21:09.310
Why's Daddy in the mud?
He won't let me play in the mud.

21:09.394 --> 21:12.147
And why isn't he in bed anyway?
Huh? Tell me that, tell me that.

21:13.773 --> 21:15.358
It's Dad! What happened?

21:15.483 --> 21:18.319
He's been up all night
trying to scare you two.

21:18.403 --> 21:21.531
-You have?
-There's nothing wrong with a good scare.

21:21.614 --> 21:23.408
You wanna grow up like me, don't ya?

21:23.491 --> 21:25.285
Fearless! Brave!

21:25.410 --> 21:28.288
Strong! Iron-willed! Dauntless!

21:28.413 --> 21:30.290
Good looking! Courageous!

21:30.415 --> 21:31.875
And unshakable!

21:34.711 --> 21:36.838
-[Pete] The Mutilator!
-[chainsaw revving]

21:36.963 --> 21:38.506
[yelling]

21:46.389 --> 21:49.726
There! That branch won't
bother anyone anymore!

21:49.851 --> 21:52.687
[laughing]

21:52.812 --> 21:56.524
[sighs] How about next week
we take in a nice puppet show?

21:56.649 --> 21:58.068
Lawn bowling perhaps.

21:58.151 --> 21:59.861
Oh, gnarly, Max.

21:59.986 --> 22:02.197
Gnarly? I can't say "gnarly."

22:02.280 --> 22:03.698
I'm not allowed to say "gnarly."

22:03.782 --> 22:05.033
How come P.J. can say "gnarly?"

22:05.116 --> 22:06.034
How come he can say "gnarly?"

22:06.117 --> 22:07.535
I said to myself... whoops!

22:07.619 --> 22:10.330
I can't say "gnarly."
I'm not allowed to say "gnarly."

22:11.873 --> 22:12.874
♪ Gimme a beat ♪

22:12.957 --> 22:14.084
[theme music playing]

22:40.443 --> 22:41.403
Yeah!
